definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  D-ribulose 5-phosphate + ATP -eq- D-ribulose 1,5-bisphosphate + ADP + 2 H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + phosphate(n) -eq- ADP + phosphate(n+1).
Catalysis of the reaction -  NAD(+) + prephenate -eq- (4-hydroxyphenyl)pyruvate + CO(2) + NADH.

Catalysis of the integration of prophage DNA into a target DNA molecule, usually a bacterial chromosome, via a sequence-specific recombination event which involves the formation of an intasome, a DNA-protein-complex designed for site-specific recombination of the phage and host DNA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + propanoate -eq- ADP + propanoyl phosphate.

Catalysis of the PEP-dependent, phosphoryl transfer-driven transport of substances across a membrane. The transport happens by catalysis of the reaction -  protein N-phosphohistidine + sugar(out) -eq- protein histidine + sugar phosphate(in). This differs from primary and secondary active transport in that the solute is modified during transport.

Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + protein L-glutamate -eq- S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + protein L-glutamate 5-methyl ester -  this reaction is the methylation of peptidyl-L-glutamate to form peptidyl-L-glutamate 5-methyl ester.
Catalysis of the reaction -  protein L-glutamate O(5)-methyl ester + H2O -eq- protein L-glutamate + methanol.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + H(2)O + pyruvate -eq- AMP + 3 H(+) + phosphate + phosphoenolpyruvate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  iminoaspartate + dihydroxy-acetone-phosphate -eq- quinolinate + 2 H2O + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + rRNA -eq- S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + rRNA containing N6-methyladenine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + rRNA -eq- S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + rRNA containing N1-methylguanine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + rRNA -eq- S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + rRNA containing N2-methylguanine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + L-rhamnulose -eq- ADP + L-rhamnulose 1-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-rhamnulose 1-phosphate -eq- glycerone phosphate + (S)-lactaldehyde.

Catalysis of the cleavage of single-stranded RNA that is monophosphorylated at its 5'-end -  cleavage occurs predominantly at 5 nucleotides from the 5'-end and in A + U-rich regions, and is blocked by the presence of a 5'-triphosphate group.

Catalysis of the cleavage of single-stranded RNA that is monophosphorylated at its 5'-end -  cleavage occurs predominantly at positions 5 and 6 nucleotides from the 5'-end and in A + U-rich regions, and is blocked by the presence of a 5'-triphosphate group.
Catalysis of the reaction -  RNA + H2O -eq- 5'-phosphomononucleotides. Cleaves RNA in the 3' to 5' direction, leaving an undigested core of 3-5 nucleotides.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2'-deoxyribonucleoside triphosphate + thioredoxin disulfide + H2O -eq- ribonucleoside triphosphate + thioredoxin.
Catalysis of the reaction -  acetyl-CoA + ribosomal-protein L-alanine -eq- CoA + ribosomal-protein N-acetyl-L-alanine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-selenocysteine + reduced acceptor -eq- hydrogen selenide + L-alanine + acceptor.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-serine + acetyl-CoA -eq- O-acetyl-L-serine + CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (Ac)2-L-Lys-D-alanyl-D-alanine + H2O -eq- (Ac)2-L-Lys-D-alanine + D-alanine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + DNA adenine -eq- S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + DNA 6-methylaminopurine.
Catalysis of the transfer of a methyl group to a DNA molecule.
Catalysis of the formation of new phosphodiester bonds between a pair of short, unique DNA target sequences.
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-sorbitol 6-phosphate + NAD+ -eq- D-fructose 6-phosphate + NADH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ADP-glucose + (1,4)-alpha-D-glucosyl(n) -eq- ADP + (1,4)-alpha-D-glucosyl(n+1).
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + streptomycin -eq- 3''-adenylylstreptomycin + diphosphate + H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  succinate semialdehyde + NAD(P)+ + H2O -eq- succinate + NAD(P)H + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  N-succinyl-LL-2,6-diaminopimelate + H(2)O -eq- LL-2,6-diaminopimelate + succinate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  N(2)-succinyl-L-arginine + 2 H(2)O + 2 H(+) -eq- N(2)-succinyl-L-ornithine + CO(2) + 2 NH(4)(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-oxoglutarate + N-succinyl-LL-2,6-diaminopimelate -eq- L-2-succinylamino-6-oxopimelate + L-glutamate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  N-succinyl-L-glutamate + H(2)O -eq- L-glutamate + succinate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  sucrose + phosphate -eq- D-fructose + alpha-D-glucose 1-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + tRNA -eq- S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + tRNA containing N1-methylguanine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + tRNA -eq- S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + tRNA containing 2'-O-methylguanosine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  tRNA(n+1) + phosphate -eq- tRNA(n) + a nucleoside diphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + D-tagatose 6-phosphate -eq- ADP + D-tagatose 1,6-bisphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-tagatose 1,6-diphosphate -eq- D-glyceraldehyde 3-phosphate + glycerone phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-altronate + NAD(+) -eq- D-tagaturonate + H(+) + NADH.
Catalysis of the reaction -  tartrate + NAD+ -eq- oxaloglycolate + NADH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2 glyoxylate + H(+) -eq- 2-hydroxy-3-oxopropanoate + CO(2).
Catalysis of the reaction -  2,3-bis(3-hydroxytetradecanoyl)-D-glucosaminyl-(1--gt-6)-beta-D-2,3-bis(3-hydroxytetradecanoyl)-beta-D-glucosaminyl 1-phosphate + ATP -eq- ADP + 2 H(+) + lipid IV(a).
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + thiamine phosphate -eq- ADP + H(+) + thiamine diphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  thymidine + phosphate -eq- thymine + 2-deoxy-D-ribose 1-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  NADH + H+ + trimethylamine-N-oxide -eq- NAD+ + trimethylamine + H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-tryptophan + H(2)O -eq- indole + NH(4)(+) + pyruvate.

Catalysis of the endonucleolytic cleavage of DNA to give random double-stranded fragments with terminal 5' or 3' protrusions -  ATP is simultaneously hydrolyzed. Cleavage is dependent on the presence in the DNA of a specific recognition site. Cleavage may occur hundreds or thousands of base pairs away from the recognition site due to translocation of DNA.

Catalysis of the endonucleolytic cleavage of DNA to give specific double-stranded fragments with terminal 5'-phosphates and 3' hydroxyls. Cleavage is dependent on the presence in the DNA of a specific recognition site -  cleavage occurs at or very near this recognition site.
